Task 2 — Employee with Department and Address Injection
🎯 Objective
Illustrate multiple bean injection in Spring 5 using setter-based dependency injection configured through AppConfig.

🧱 Class-wise Design
1️.Department Class

Attributes:

int deptId

String deptName

Methods:

Setter methods and showDepartment().

2️.Address Class

Attributes:

String city

String country

Methods:

Setter methods and showAddress().

3️. Employee Class

Attributes:

int empId

String empName

Department department

Address address

Methods:

Setter methods for all fields.

showEmployeeDetails() method to display all info.

4️.AppConfig Class

Responsibilities:

Annotated with @Configuration.

Define beans for Department, Address, and Employee.

Inject both supporting beans (Department, Address) into the Employee bean.

5️. MainApp Class

Responsibilities:

Load Spring context.

Get Employee bean.

Call showEmployeeDetails().

📘 Expected Output:
---------------------
Employee ID: 101, Name: Rohit Sharma
Department: IT
Address: Pune, India
